    "also variously known as the arrival time or the Fermat potential, is a central concept in gravitational lensing.",
    "As we have seen, the lens equation is the zero-gradient condition on the time delay.",
    "The second and higher derivatives are also important, as detailed later.",
    "Fermat's principle in gravitational lensing was introduced using different approaches by Schneider (1985) and Blandford and Narayan (1986).",
    "Expressions like (8) do, however, appear in earlier work (Cooke and Kantowski 1975; Borgeest 1983) albeit without the interpretation as Fermat's principle."
